<br>
Last time I checked, America was founded by religious outcasts from Europe... people who fled their homelands in order to be able to practice their religious beliefs.<br>
<br>
These people believed in God.  His size, shape, and temperment varied a bit from demonination to demonination... but it all came back to God... and the freedom to worship him in the manner that people chose to do so.<br>
<br>
To deny this, is to deny the very foundations of American society.<br>
<br>
In the American society, we have norms... for right or wrong.  You are free to be a Jew, Christian, Athiest, etc... but the bottom line is that this freedom is the direct result of God, and people who came here to worship him.<br>
<br>
Included in your freedoms is the freedom to pack up and leave.  If you're unhappy with the use of the word &quot;God&quot;, or it's implications, why not try Great Britain?  No?  How about Russia?  No?  Hmmm... what about Iran?  Naw.  Turkey?  Yeah!  Turkey is a wonderful place.<br>
<br>
Have a nice day, and ummm... God bless you.<br>
